               <p>GEORGE THOMAS LLOYD. I work at Mr. Bowerbanks', in Sun-street. These shirts were in a box in my room, in <placeName id="t18261026-56-crimeloc316">Long-alley</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18261026-56-crimeloc316" type="placeName" value="Long-alley"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18261026-56-crimeloc316" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18261026-56-off314 t18261026-56-crimeloc316"></join> - I have known the prisoner six years, and as he was in distress, I asked him to breakfast with me; on the 22d of September, between eight and nine o'clock, when I came home, I found him there, and left him there with my wife; when I returned at night, she missed the shirts; one was afterwards found in pawn, and the other on his person - I had a very good opinion of him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18261026-56-person478">
